<br>
This is not a flame either.  Nor is it a statement of policy for my guild.  It just something you might want to try to understand when you mention how hard you tried to get on one of these &quot;high end&quot; raids without success.  By &quot;high end&quot; I'll assume you mean &quot;killing an ubermob&quot; no matter which guild or organizer is running the show.<br>
<br>
I can only speak to the practices of Silent Redemption, but I suspect that most any of the &quot;larger&quot; or &quot;more uber&quot; guilds on the server would handle things in roughly similar fashion.  I imagine you would handle things in roughly similar fashion were you the raid organizer in question.  All you have to do is consider how you'd fill out a raid roster.<br>
<br>
First, you take your guild brothers and sisters (guildmembers).  Second, you take your friends who want to be part of the family (recruits, to not put too fine a point on it.)  Finally, you fill out your raid roster with people you know to be good, solid players who belong to the classes necessary to your success.  If you're short clerics, you invite clerics.  If you're short warriors, you invite warriors.  If you're short bards, you invite bards.  <br>
<br>
If you're not short anyone and you have what it takes, you stop at the &quot;family and friends&quot; point and you don't invite anyone.  This has nothing to do with not liking someone or not wanting someone present.  Its simple logic.  Once you have the force necessary to dispatch the mob and you've invited everyone to whom you and your guild are indebted for their service on previous raids, adding more players to the mix is, perhaps sadly, superfluous.  <br>
<br>
The only advice I can give to you is &quot;keep trying.&quot;  Will you ever get on a Silent Redemption raid?  I don't know.  Will you ever get on an Enshadowed raid?  I don't know.  All I can say is that you'll be more likely to get on one of these raids by asking if there's room to be included than you will by remaining silent.  Of course, the other alternative also exists: you could run one of these raids yourself.<br>
<br>
Whichever course you choose, good luck. <p><BR>
